<HEADLINE> Sudan Starts Exporting Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, August 30 (Xinhua) -- For the first time in its
history, Sudan exported oil Monday to the world market and the
first consignment consisting of 600,000 barrels left for
Singapore, Sudanese President Omar al-Bashir said.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in a rally at the Bashaer seaport, 25
kilometers from the port city of Bur Sudan in northeast Sudan.
</P>
<P>
In his address, Bashir described the event as a great
achievement made by the Sudanese people.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he underlined Sudan's rejection of all foreign
dictations and threats.
</P>
<P>
The oil exploitation project is a giant investment that
cost some 2 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sudan's oil reserve is estimated at 800 million barrels.
</P>
</TEXT>
