<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Urged to Utilize Potential Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Water Resources
Minister Shiferaw Jarso has urged to develop water resources in
the country and help more people to have access to clean water.
</P>
<P>
Only 20 percent of the total population of 60 million has
access to potable water, and the sanitation coverage is even at
much low percentage, Shiferaw told the 25th International Water
Engineering Development Conference that began here Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to environmental health expert Gebre-Amanuel Teka, 46
percent of child mortality is caused by unsafe water supply and
lack of sanitation.
</P>
<P>
"Failure to have access to safe water supply and simple hygiene
would constitute for nearly 80 percent water-borne and related
diseases," he said in his paper submitted to the conference.
</P>
<P>
About 500 participants, from 32 countries are attending the
five-day conference under the theme "Integrated Development for
Water Supply and Sanitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
