<HEADLINE> Albania Attaches Importance to Its Ties with Hungary: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli
Majko said here on Monday that the Albanian government considered
important its ties with Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Majko made this remark when he met Hungarian Prime Minister
Orban Viktor, who arrived here on Monday on a one-day visit to the
country.
</P>
<P>
This importance becomes more touchable as the two countries
</P>
<P>
are moving in the same direction according to the principles
set
</P>
<P>
in the Stability Pact for Southeast Europe.
</P>
<P>
It is the first visit of its kind since the 1960s as described
by Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli Majko, who urged the two
countries to develop their ties in various fields, especially the
bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Orban said that with the admission of Hungary into the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), his country paid special
attention to the developments in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need for strengthening economic ties
between Hungary and Albania.
</P>
<P>
Albanian President Rexhep Meidani Monday also met with Orban
and the two expressed the desire of both countries to reinforce
bilateral cooperation by exploiting all possible spaces.
</P>
<P>
During Orban's stay in Albania, the governments of the two
countries agreed to set up a joint economic commission in November
to promote bilateral trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
