<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Shoots Down Unidentified Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian anti-aircraft
forces have downed an unidentified aircraft when it was
penetrating into Ethiopian airspace, a military spokesperson said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft was downed at a point about 30 km South of Adwa at
5:00 PM local time Sunday when it moved deep inside the Ethiopian
no-fly zone from Eritrea's airspace, the spokesperson of the
Ministry of Defense said.
</P>
<P>
Adwa is a border town in northern Tigray State.
</P>
<P>
Professionals of the Ethiopian Defense are gathering
information about the downed aircraft, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Eritrea have been at war since May last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
