<HEADLINE> African Regional Anti-poaching Team Catches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The Nairobi-based Lusaka
Agreement Task Force (LATF) has rounded up poachers near the
Tanzania-Kenya border and seized their rifles, according a news
release from its headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The three poachers caught on August 27 are in police custody in
Arusha in northern Tanzania for questioning, an official of the
task force said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Many elephants have been poached in Kenya's Tsavo West National
Park and Tanzania's Mkomazi National Reserve in recent months,
according to the release.
</P>
<P>
LATF Director Adan Dullo noted that the arrests followed weeks
of intelligence work and the key to the success was partnership.
</P>
<P>
LATF was launched on June 1 this year under the Lusaka
Agreement in 1992,
</P>
<P>
which charges the task force to curb cross-border poaching with
national wildlife law enforcement agencies of its signatories,
including Kenya, Tanzania, Lesotho, Republic of the Congo and
other five nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
