<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Condemns Sanaa Blasts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia condemned
on Monday the explosion that shattered a supermarket in
Yemen's capital city of Sanaa and caused scores of human
casualties on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi cabinet, during a session chaired by Crown Prince
and Deputy Prime Minister Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz, denounced
"the subversive activities, which can only be done by those
who don't want welfare for Yemen and the Yemeni people."
</P>
<P>
At least six people were killed and 12 others injured when a
booby-trapped car exploded in Sanaa on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Prince Abdullah, during the cabinet meeting, also offered his
country's support to every effort employed in maintaining peace
and stability in every corner of the world, the Kuwait News
Agency reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
