<HEADLINE> S. African Trade Fair Hopes to Boost African Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 30 (Xinhua) -- South African International
Trade Exhibition (Saitex) hopes to further stimulate growing trade
figures between South Africa and the rest of Africa, organizers
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Figures show that Africa is a major and growing export market
for us," said Saitex Director John Theron.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's export market has increased 335 percent since
the lifting of international sanctions in 1993, with the rest of
Africa being one of its most important markets.
</P>
<P>
South Africa maintains an overall trade surplus with the rest
of Africa of 5:1, and eight of its top 15 trading partners in
Africa are from Sub- Saharan Africa.
</P>
<P>
A number of African states are expected to be among the 38
countries exhibiting at Saitex, which will be held from 19 to 23
October.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Trade and Industry's Export Week seminars and
 workshops will also be run alongside the exhibition this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
