<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Cape Peninsula to Be Declared Disaster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 30 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki would declare the tornado-ravaged suburbs of Cape Town
in the Cape Peninsula a disaster area, the president's office said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The declaration was based on the recommendation of Welfare
Minister Zola Skweyiya, who toured the area on Sunday,
presidential aide Parks Mankahlana said.
</P>
<P>
Skweyiya told reporters after the tour that he viewed the
disaster as a " national emergency".
</P>
<P>
Five people were killed, 119 injured and 5,000 left homeless
when the " twister" struck just before dawn on Sunday. Of the
injured, 110 were being treated and nine were lightly hurt.
</P>
</TEXT>
