<HEADLINE> Jordanian-Kuwaiti Talks to Focus on Better </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's King Abdullah Bin
Hussein, who is expected to be here for an official visit early
next month, will focus his talks with Kuwaiti leaders on ways of
strengthening bilateral ties, Jordan's new ambassador to Kuwait
said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the two countries will also discuss means of
upgrading bilateral cooperation in various fields, said Mohammed
Al-Mufdhi Al-Qaraan, who was appointed on Sunday as Jordan's first
ambassador to Kuwait since the 1991 Gulf war triggered by Iraq's
invasion of Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
King Abdullah is scheduled to make his first visit to Kuwait on
September 6, according to local media reports.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming summit between Kuwait and Jordan will also touch
upon a number of issues of mutual concern, the situation in the
region and the Middle East peace process, Al-Qaraan said in an
interview with the official Kuwait news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian diplomat stated that the current circumstances
are ready for the restoration of relations between Jordan and
Kuwait to the level before the Iraqi occupation. But he did not
elaborate.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Jordan were estranged from each other after Amman
showed apparent sympathy with Iraq during the 1991 Gulf war.
</P>
<P>
Jordan reopened its embassy in Kuwait last March, during an
official visit here by Jordanian Foreign Minister Abdul Ilah
Al-Khatib, marking a normalization of ties between the two Arab
nations.
</P>
<P>
There were reports that Kuwait has named its ambassador to
Amman, but the reports have not been officially confirmed.
</P>
</TEXT>
