<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Killed as Bandits Ambush Lorry in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 30 (Xinhua) -- A group of armed bandits
have ambushed a lorry in a district in northwest Tanzania's Kagera
Region, killing a man, injuring two others and taking away cash
and properties.
</P>
<P>
Kagera Regional Police Commander, Eliuko Elihaki, said Monday
that the lorry was ambushed while ascending a hill along
Rusahunga-nyakahula road in Biharamulo district at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The police commander said one of the suspects who was armed
with a sub- machine gun, fired bullets at the tires forcing the
driver Amani Tamim to stop.
</P>
<P>
 After the lorry stopped, five other bandits who were armed
with machetes jumped out of the bush and forced the passengers to
get off and hand over to them everything they had, Elihaki said.
</P>
<P>
He said one passenger, Ally Msumba, tried to disarm a bandit a
machete but was shot on the stomach by another bandit. The man
died on the spot.
</P>
<P>
Two other people in the lorry sustained injuries and have been
admitted to a hospital. The passengers also surrendered 700 U.S.
dollars, three million shillings (about 3,750 U.S. dollars) and
two bags, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The lorry was travelling from Bukoba, capital of the Kagera
Region to Bukavu in the east part of the Democratic republic of
Congo, Elihaki said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
