<HEADLINE> Mozambique Launches Polio Vaccination Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano Monday officially launched the second phase of the
country's 1999 anti- polio vaccination campaign in the Maputo
suburb of Chamanculo.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Chamanculo crowd, Chissano urged the entire
Mozambican population to cooperate with the health services in the
quest to eradicate poliomyelitis.
</P>
<P>
He called on all adults to take their children aged under five
to the vaccination brigades.
</P>
<P>
Chissano also symbolically launched the campaign by
administering the oral vaccine to some of the children waiting
there.
</P>
<P>
Mocambique's health authorities believe that the country may be
awarded by the World Health Organization (WHO) the certificate as
free from polio by the year 2000 if the current vaccination
efforts keep going.
</P>
<P>
According to Health Minister Aurelio Zilhao, the coverage of
the first- phase vaccination campaign, which was launched between
July 26-30, reached some 114 percent of the target figure.
</P>
<P>
For the second phase, the authorities are paying special
attention to Maputo and other areas falling below the average
coverage rate in July.  
</P>
