<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Fall Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks fell
sharply Monday as investors were concerned with the future
course of interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 176.04 at
10,914.13. The blue chip index lost 235.87 points in the
two previous sessions.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also lower. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index fell 24.25 at 1,324.02 and the technology
heavy Nasdaq index fell 46.21 at 2,712.69.
</P>
<P>
The stocks plunged because investors remained nervous
about interest rates. Last Friday, the Federal Reserve Alan
Greenspan voiced concerns over the highly valued stock market,
triggering fears of possibility of the third rates increase and
pushing the stocks lower.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve raised the rates twice in the past two
months but stocks rose sharply after the decisions on rates hike
were announced.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 10.58 at 615.13 and the American Stock
Exchange index fell 7.31 at 775.21. The Russell 2000 index fell
5.09 at 427.36.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 5-to-2 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 2,151 down, 861 up and 517
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increase to 595.57 million shares from 553.19
million in the previous sessions. 
</P>
