<HEADLINE> Major Task of Serb Republic is to Keep Social Stableness: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The major task of the Yugoslav
Serb Republic is to maintain social and economic stability,
Foreign Minister Mirko Marjanovich said on Tuesday when he visited
Zrenjanin city in Vojvodina Autonomous Province.
</P>
<P>
Despite the impact of NATO's airstrikes against Yugoslavia and
international sanctions during the past eight months, the Serb
Republic government has maintained market stability by allowing
prices to fluctuate within a 2 percent margin, and insuring the
living standard of civilians, Marjanovich said when he met with
local officials.
</P>
<P>
The government will continue to pursue the stability policy. It
will also try its best to ensure gasoline supplies, children's
welfare and salary payments.
</P>
<P>
Marjanovich stressed that problem of housing those who lost
their residences must be settled before November.
</P>
<P>
The rehabilitation is going well in many regions as bridges,
roads, railways and other basic facilities destroyed by NATO's
bombs have been rebuilt, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government will put 800 million dinars (about 70 million U.
S. dollars) into the restoration of the power system -- which
suffered heavy damages during the airstrikes -- to ensure heating
service in the winter, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
