accord in Lusaka on July 10, but the RCD did not seal the pact
over disagreement which faction should sign on its behalf.
</P>
<P>
It was decided that the founding members of the split RCD would
come to Zambia to sign the accord in late August, which would pave
the way for the deployment of international peace-keepers and
direct talks between the Kinshasa government and political and
military groups opposing its rule.
</P>
<P>
The civil war in former Zaire broke out on August 2 last year,
and the RCD rebels have been backed by Uganda and Rwanda while
Zimbabwe, Namibia and Angola sent troops to fight on the side of
Congolese President Laurent Kabila.  
