<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills 17 in E. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen people have been
confirmed dead in a big landslide in Uganda's eastern district of
Mbale Monday.
</P>
<P>
The landslide, which occurred in the morning, was triggered by
a heavy downpour in the area, local media reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the heavy rain washed away makeshift bridges
linking two sub-counties to the main road.
</P>
<P>
The bridges were constructed to assist and transport essential
household commodities after last year's landslide which killed 35
people and left over 2,000 others homeless.
</P>
<P>
Seven bodies have so far been recovered and six survivors have
been admitted to local hospitals, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
