<HEADLINE> President: Latvia Likely to Join EU within Finnish Presidency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Latvian President-Elect
VairaVike Freiberga said Tuesday that her country is likely to
join the European Union (EU) during the Finnish presidency.
</P>
<P>
After a talk with Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari, Freiberga,
the first female Latvian president ever elected, said that she was
encouraged by the EU leader's comment that her country has made
positive progress on the course of joining EU.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on Latvia's security policy, Freiberga rejected the
possibility of applying for Russian assistance on solving domestic
problems, stressing that Latvia is an independent country pursuing
its own security plans.
</P>
<P>
Freiberga said her government attaches great emphasis on
joining EU and NATO, while maintaining friendly relations with
Russia. 
