<HEADLINE> EC Provides India With 200 Million ECU for Health Care </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
will provide financial assistance of 200 million European currency
units (211 million U.S. dollars) for health and family welfare
programs in India.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect was signed Tuesday between the
Indian government and the EC in Shimla, a summer resort 340
kilometers north of here.
</P>
<P>
The assistance would be provided for programs like reproductive
and child health care in the north state of Himachal, according to
the Press Trust of India (PTI).
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a government spokesman as saying that the
investment phase would run for four years beginning from the
coming October.
</P>
<P>
The assistance would be made available to the state government
for the reproductive and child health programs administered by the
central government, the spokesman said. 
