<HEADLINE> Pakistan Looks Forward to East Timor-like Referendum in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif Tuesday said referendum in East Timor has raised his hope
for a matching development in Indian-held Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Sharif was addressing a public meeting at Nilabut of
Pakistan-held Kashmir, organized every year to commemorate the
launching of movement against Indian rule 52 years ago.
</P>
<P>
"Now, it's the turn of Kashmir where plebiscite is to be held,"
he said amid applause from the public.
</P>
<P>
He said Kashmir would become part of Pakistan after its
"liberation from the clutches of India".
</P>
<P>
Sharif said Pakistan wants a negotiated and respectable
solution to the Kashmir dispute which has emerged as "a nuclear
flash point".
</P>
<P>
He accused India of continued "worst human rights violations"
in the occupied valley, adding that "the day is not far away when
the Kashmiri blood will crown with success." 
</P>
</TEXT>
