<HEADLINE> DPRK Criticizes Japan For Exaggerating DPRK Missile Threat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The official media of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) on Tuesday criticized
Japan for claiming the DPRK represented a missile threat to its
country.
</P>
<P>
Japan's claim that the DPRK was a threat to the region is "
sheer fiction" which is aimed at painting the country as a nuclear
threat and to justify its hostile policy, said the Korean Central
News Agency (KCNA) in a commentary.
</P>
<P>
The commentary was issued to mark the first anniversary of a
satellite launch on August 31 last year.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said, Japan "made a far-fetched assertion" that
"neither missile launch nor satellite launch in the DPRK can be
allowed."
</P>
<P>
"Their final aim is to realize their ambition to become a
military and nuclear power at an early date and strengthen '
cooperation' with the United States and the Republic of Korea in a
bid to thoroughly isolate and stifle the DPRK," it said.
</P>
<P>
The KCNA commentary said history had shown Japan to be the
aggressor, recalling the brutal 1910-45 colonial rule of the
Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
"If they dare provoke a war, we will not miss the opportunity
to seek revenge upon the enemy," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
