<HEADLINE> Silver Prices Drop Sharply in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Silver prices dropped sharply
Tuesday on the bullion market in Mumbai (Bombay) due to poor
industrial demand.
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) resumed weak at 8,025 rupees
(186.63 U.S. dollars) per kilogram and declined further to end at
8,010 rupees (186.27 U.S. dollars), showing a fall of 50 rupees
(1.16 U.S. dollars) over the last close of 8,060 rupees (187.44
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, raw silver (.916 fineness) declined by 25 rupees
(0.58 U.S. dollars) to 7,890 rupees (183.49 U.S. dollars) per kg
from 7,915 rupees (184.07 U.S. dollars) and tenderable silver
dropped to 8,015 rupees (186.39 U.S. dollars) per kg from 8,065
rupees (187.56 U.S. dollars). 
