<HEADLINE> HK Mortgage Lending Slower in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- New mortgage lending in Hong
Kong declined in July, according to the Hong Kong Monetary
Authority's (HKMA) monthly survey of residential mortgage lending.
</P>
<P>
The amount of gross new loans made in July decreased by 13.5
percent to 12.2 billion HK dollars (1.56 billion U.S. dollars)
from 14.1 billion HK dollars (1.80 billion U.S. dollars) in June.
The average size of new loans decreased to 1.49 million HK dollars
(191,025 U.S. dollars) in July from 1.58 million HK dollars (202,
564 U.S. dollars) in June.
</P>
<P>
New loans approved during the month decreased by 32.6 percent
to 10.5 billion HK dollars (1.34 billion U.S. dollars) from the 15.
6 billion HK dollars (2 billion U.S. dollars) in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
