<HEADLINE> Banks in Shanghai Expanding Cooperation with Overseas Counterparts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Pudong Development
Bank (SPDB) signed contracts with three foreign banks today to
bolster their efforts to expand Renminbi yuan-based businesses.
</P>
<P>
The three foreign banks, the French Credit Lyonnais SA, the U.S.
-based Bank of America, and the Japanese Daiichi Kangyo Bank, will
receive a total of 160 million yuan (19 million US dollars) in
interbank loans from SPDB.
</P>
<P>
All four of the banks also planned to increase their
cooperation in interbank loans and project financing, and will
soon grant 400 million yuan in syndicated loans to several local
firms.
</P>
<P>
Financial experts said that China has granted licenses to 19
overseas banks to start yuan-based business since March 1997,
however, these foreign banks lack sufficient operating funds for
such business.
</P>
<P>
Many Chinese commercial banks in Shanghai, China's largest
trade and financial center, have taken steps to increase
cooperation with foreign counterparts soon after the central bank
announced it would expand foreign banks' scope of Renminbi
business.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Communications, the Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China, the Agricultural Bank of China and CITIC Bank of China
have all started interbank loaning with foreign banks in Shanghai.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
