<HEADLINE> Kyrgyzstan Has Enough Force to Wipe out Armed Islamic Invaders: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister Muratbek
Imanaliyev said Kyrgyzstan has enough force to wipe out armed
Islamic invaders, the Kyrgyz Telegraph Agency quoted him as saying
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Kyrgyz troops have successfully prevented the gunmen from
entering into its backland, Imanaliyev said.
</P>
<P>
About 600 to 1,000 Islamic gunmen entered Batken and Chon-
Alaisky regions in southern Kyrgyzstan from Tajikistan two weeks
ago. They held 16 hostages including four Japanese geologists and
a Kyrgyz general.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen are thought to be advancing to Uzbekistan to carry
out terrorist acts.
</P>
<P>
Foreign and defense ministers from Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan,
Kazakhstan and Tajikistan met in the southern Kyrgyz city of Osh
on August 28 to discuss joint military action against the
terrorists.
</P>
<P>
The other three countries promised to provide support,
including weapons, to Kyrgyz government troops to flush out the
Islamic gunmen. 
</P>
