<HEADLINE> Russia to Aid Kyrgyzstan Fighting Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian Defense Minister Igor
Sergeyev will fly to Tashkent Wednesday to discuss with leaders of
Uzbekistan ways to help Kyrgyzstan fight Islamic militants that
roam Kyrgyzstan and the Central Asian region as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Bishkek has officially requested Russian military assistance
to eliminate a large formation of militants entrenched in
southwest Kyrgyzstan, the Interfax news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
