<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Ecuadorian President (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji said here
today during a meeting with visiting Ecuadorian President Jamil
Mahuad that China is ready to develop friendly relations of
cooperation with all Latin American countries.
</P>
<P>
All countries and regions across the world are developing by
their own momentum, he said, adding that Latin America is a
continent full of hope.
</P>
<P>
Although it is faced with difficulties in its economic growth,
it embraces a bright future, Zhu explained.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier called Mahuad's visit to China a "major
event" in China-Ecuador relations, saying it will help increase
mutual understanding and friendship and put bilateral relations on
a vigorous growth track.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorian president noted that his visit came at a time
close to the 50th birth anniversary of the People's Republic of
China and the 20th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic
relations between China and Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
He described the visit as "very successful" and having pushed
forward cooperation in various areas between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
While Zhu said that multi-polarization is an irreversible trend
of the world and the world cannot fall under the influence of one
or two countries, Mahuad stressed that it is "not a good thing"
that the world affairs fall under the monopoly of any single
nation.
</P>
<P>
Mahuad said the world should be a multi-polarized one.
</P>
</TEXT>
