<HEADLINE> Chinese Lifters Set New Asian Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, China, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongman Wan
Jianhui broke the snatch Asian record in the 69kg division only
two minutes after compatriot Zhang Guozheng shattered the Asian
mark at the Asian Weightlifting Championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Zhang snatched 155 kilograms in his third
attempt, bettering the listed Asian record by 2.5kg.
</P>
<P>
One minute later, Wan added 2.5kg to Zhang's new record and
successfully set a new mark of snatch in 157.5kg.
</P>
<P>
Wan, 24, from Fujian Province, took the overall title of 342.
5kg and silver medal in the clean and jerk for 185kg while Zhang
claimed the jerk victory with the same weight by was awarded as
winner in favor of his lighter weight.
</P>
<P>
"Zhang performed better than the Wan today though he is elder
than Wan. Zhang had just graduated from university last year and
still has potentials to develop," said Yang Hanxiong, head coach
of the Chinese national team.
</P>
<P>
Ri Song-Hui of Korea collected two out of the three gold medals
in the women's 58kg class when she topped the clean and jerk with
125.0kg for a winning total of 220.0kg.
</P>
<P>
Kuo Ping-Chun from Chinese Taipei grabbed the snatch title in
95.0kg and totaled for the third in 210.0kg while Xu Xiongying of
China won the silver in the overall with 212.5kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
