<HEADLINE> Double-Decker Train Manufactured in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Production of an air-conditioned
double-decker train, the most advanced of its kind in China, was
finished today in this capital city of Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The train, which was manufactured in Nanjing, will be ready for
operation on the rail line between Nanjing, Shanghai and Hangzhou
by October 1. Hangzhou is the capital city of east China's
Zhejiang Province, while Shanghai is China's largest metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The train has two engines, one at each end, and nine cars. It
can carry a total of 1,140 passengers and reach a speed of 180
kilometers per hour. 
</P>
