<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Students in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen Chinese academics who
study in France today completed a nine-day poverty-relief program
in southwest China's Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Ministry of Education and the Chinese Embassy
in France, the program was established in June in Paris to improve
scientific and technological development in Guizhou and help local
poor people.
</P>
<P>
The program, which started on August 23, included 20 lectures
about the province's economic resources, scientific research,
poverty analysis and development potential.
</P>
