<DOCNO> XIE19990831.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen, Vanuatu Deputy PM Confer in Beijing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qian said that cooperation in economic, trade, medical, health
and cultural areas in recent years has been satisfactory, adding
that as China and Vanuatu are both developing countries in the
Asia-Pacific region, the growth of their cooperative ties is not
only in the fundamental interests of the people of the two
countries, but also conducive to peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
China always holds that countries, big or small, rich or poor,
strong or weak, should be equal, and should have the right to
participate in all international affairs on an equal footing, Qian
said.
</P>
<P>
Jimmy said that China has offered valuable support and
assistance for Vanuatu over the past years, which promoted the
implementation of its comprehensive economic reform plan and
economic growth, adding that Vanuatu is grateful for that.
</P>
<P>
He said that Vanuatu pays close attention to its ties with
China, and it is fully prepared to develop relations with China
oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two sides signed an agreement on economic
and technical cooperation.  
</P>
