<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deposits Increase in Hong Kong in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Statistics published Tuesday
by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority show that both total deposits
and total loans and advances increased during the month of July.
</P>
<P>
Total deposits registered a steady growth of 2.0 percent in
July.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong dollar deposits increased slightly by 0.1 percent in
July. Among different categories, time deposits saw a steady
increase of 1.8 percent, while demand and savings deposits dropped
by 4.0 percent and 3.6 percent respectively in July.
</P>
<P>
Foreign currency deposits grew by 4.6 percent in July.
</P>
<P>
Total loans and advances saw a marginal rise of 0.1 percent in
July, reversing the downtrend which started in November 1998. The
rise in total loans was attributable to an increase in loans for
use outside Hong Kong (up 1.4 percent).
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, domestic loans continued to decline in July
by 0.5 percent, but at a more moderate pace when compared with
previous months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
