<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 31 (Xinhua) --The Australian dollar finished
Tuesday's trade considerably stronger, boosted by better than
expected balance on goods and services data.
</P>
<P>
The Australian currency finished the session at 63.73 U.S.
cents from yesterday's close of 63.25 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Bureau of Statistics reported Tuesday that the
balance on goods and services (BOGS) in the month narrowed to an
adjusted 604 million U.S. dollars, from an upwardly revised 1.02
billion U.S. dollars in June.
</P>
<P>
the Australian dollar was buying 0.6065 euro from 0.6042 at
Monday's close and 70.68 Japanese yen from 70.16. 
