<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Down 1.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks lost 205.89
points, or 1.5 percent, to close at 13,482.77 Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said there was no further good news and the market had
no unified direction and they blamed the weakness on the U.S.
downturn on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover was 6.186 billion HK dollars (792 million U.
S. dollars), 583 million HK dollars (75 million U.S. dollars) less
than Monday's turnover of 6.769 billion HK dollars (867 million U.
S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Finance Counter, Utilities, Properties and Commerce and
Industry made across-the-board decreases of 1.54 percent, 0.42
percent, 2.14 percent and 2.1 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index up 0.66 percent and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index up 0.27 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks opened up 113.68 points, or 0.83 percent, at
13,574.95 Tuesday and closed the morning session at 13,531.75.
</P>
</TEXT>
