<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Down 1.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Karachi, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Karachi Stocks fell Tuesday on
news that Water and Power Development Authority (WAPDA) has
refused to accept the offer of Hub Power Company (Hubco) regarding
cut in tariff rates, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The 100-share price index of Karachi Stock Exchange closed
14.81 points or 1.22 percent lower, to 1,206.51 points against
Monday's 1,221.35.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume Tuesday stood at 132.292 million shares
against Monday's 125.119 million shares.
</P>
<P>
The market reacted negatively on news that WAPDA's chairman has
termed Hubco's offer of cut in tariff rates "unacceptable", which
indicates that the tariff dispute is yet to be resolved, said
dealers.
</P>
<P>
Hubco, the largest private sector power producer with a
weightage of 18 percent of the 100-share index, fell by 0.45
rupees, or 2.39 percent, to 18.35 rupees from 18.80 rupees.
</P>
<P>
Out of the all 181 active issues, losers beat gainers 81 to 47
while 53 remained unchanged. 
</P>
