<HEADLINE> Pakistan Foils Indian Attack on Disputed Border: Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani troops foiled Indian
army's attempt to capture a Pakistani post in the disputed area of
Kashmir, said an Pakistan army statement issued here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Backed by heavy artillery fire, Indian soldiers crossed the
Line of Control into Pakistan-administered area Monday to launch a
ground assault on a post in Shyok-Turtok sector, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred near Kargil where Pakistan and India troops
waged a bitter battle this summer.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani soldiers beefed up a defensive and a large number of
enemy troops were killed and injured, according to the army
statement. Three Pakistani soldiers were killed. 
</P>
