<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Tumble on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices nose-dived on the
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday with profit-taking hurting the
market sentiment mostly.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) plunged by 34.21 points
to end at 2,117.17 points in low trading.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 209.84 million shares worth 386.81
million Singapore dollars (230.01 million U.S. dollars). Losers
outstripped gainers by 300 to 42 with 102 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 19.38 million parcel by Gen Int which
was transacted at 0.39 U.S. dollars per share. It was followed by
IPSCOM which had 13.67 million stocks done. AFP was the next with
12.38 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
PacCent was the most active stock picking up 30 cents to close
at 7.30 Singapore dollars. Global w02 climbed 29 cents to finish
at 1.38 Singapore dollars. OCBC and Venture moved up 20 cents to
end at 11.20 and 16.10 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SIA DBSw00 was the biggest loser of the day
shedding 60 cents to close at 9.25 Singapore dollars. SIA 200, SPH
and UOB F sank 50 cents each to finish at 15.50, 28.00 and 12.50
Singapore dollars respectively. CityDev retreated 40 cents to end
at 10.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed Tuesday's fall to profit-taking, Wall
Street's overnight drop and decline in regional bourses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
