<HEADLINE> Nearly Half of Mobile Phone Users in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Of all 13,000 mobile phone
subscribers in Ethiopia, 6,000 have cancelled their subscriptions,
Ethiopian Telecommunication Corporation (ETC) disclosed on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The cancellations were due to high tariff and the high down
payments of the cellphone service, an official of the state-owned
corporation said.
</P>
<P>
With a capacity to serve 50,000 subscribers, the ETC is now
offering service to only 7,000 users mainly due to the high tariff
rate of about nine U.S. cents per minute.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of potential subscribers could not keep up the
payment, said an official of the corporation.
</P>
<P>
The corporation said it had undertaken a study on possibilities
of tariff reduction to increase the number of clients.
</P>
<P>
Abebe Gashaw, senior official of the Ethiopian
Telecommunication Corporation, said there may be tariff reduction
following approval of the study by the board.  
</P>
</TEXT>
