<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate in Macao Climbs Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Macao's unemployment rate from May
to July this year rose to 6.4 percent, statistics released Tuesday
by the Macao Census and Statistics Department show.
</P>
<P>
The figure was 0.1 percentage point higher than that during the
April-June period of this year and an increase of 1.7 percentage
points over the same period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Macao has been suffering from economic difficulties over the
past years and many people expect that Macao's forthcoming return
to the motherland will bring about brighter prospects.
</P>
<P>
Trade unions and other social bodies have urged the government
to create more jobs and cut the number of laborers coming from
elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, a government labor department issued a
circular requiring that employers who want to hire new workers get
registered at the department and give local people preferential
choices. However, the circular is not compulsory.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the new graduates who joined in the work force this
summer also exerted more employment pressure to some extent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
