<HEADLINE> Macao to Host 11th International Fireworks Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The 11th Macao International
Fireworks Display Contest will be held here from mid-September to
early October, a tourism official said at a press conference on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Rodolfo Faustino, director of the Macao Government Tourist
Office, said ten teams from the Philippines, Australia, Germany,
Thailand, Britain, Switzerland, Portugal, Japan and China's
mainland and Taiwan will take part in the contest.
</P>
<P>
The teams will give fireworks shows on the nights of September
11, 18, 25 and October 1 and 5. Each night, two teams will stage
shows lasting about 18 minutes.
</P>
<P>
To enliven the life of local residents and attract more
tourists, Macao started the international fireworks display
contest in 1989. In the first six contests, five teams
participated each year and the number of teams rose to 10 in 1995.
</P>
