<BODY>
<HEADLINE> E. Timor Police Request More Personnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- East Timor Police Chief Col.
Timbul Silaen Tuesday requested five companies of police personnel
from the Indonesian Police to anticipate "the worst situation"
following the vote count on August 30.
</P>
<P>
According to the Antara News Agency, Silaen made the request
following his meeting with visiting Irish Foreign Affairs Minister
David Andrews, who visited Dili, capital of East Timor, as the
official ballot observer of the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Silaen said some police personnel who have long served in East
Timor will be relieved.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian government has deployed about 20,000 policemen
and security personnel to safeguard the process of polling. A high
turnout of voters marked the United Nations-organized ballot on
the future of East Timor which ended remarkably peacefully on
Monday, defying fears of violence voiced by many.
</P>
<P>
However, East Timor Military District Commander Col. Noer Muis
was concerned over possible violence following the ballot.
</P>
<P>
"The post-ballot period will be a very critical stage since
neither of the two conflicting factions seems able to accept the
possibility of defeat. And this has been reflected by the numerous
clashes among their supporters during the campaigning," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Antara, ballot boxes began arriving in Dili on
Tuesday. The sealed boxes will be taken to the Dili Museum
building in Comoro, next to the building of the East Timor
regional police.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Mission in East Timor (UNAMET) spokesman David Wimhurst
said the results of the voting would be announced one week after
the ballot.
</P>
<P>
The referendum under an agreement among Indonesia, Portugal and
the United Nations was for voters to choose between special
autonomy within Indonesia and independence.
</P>
<P>
East Timor, a former Portuguese colony annexed by Indonesia in
1976, has been seen by the U.N. General Assembly as a
non-self-governing territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
