<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Chinese Premier Meets Turkmenistan Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji told
Batyr Sarjayev, deputy prime minister and defense minister of
Turkmenistan, that China is willing to carry out more active
cooperation with his country and lift the relationship to a new
level on the basis of mutual respect, benefit and equality.
</P>
<P>
"During the past seven years since the two countries forged
diplomatic ties, the friendly relationship saw smooth development
with cooperation expanding in all fields," Zhu said in his meeting
this afternoon with Sarjayev, the first Turkmenistan defense
minister to pay a visit to China.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side was satisfied with such a good development
momentum, he added.
</P>
<P>
Sarjayev told his host that Turkmenistan highly values its
cooperation with China in all areas especially military and
economic. As defense minister, he said he could also learn from
the experience of China's army construction.
</P>
<P>
He conveyed the regards of Turkmenistan President Saparmurad
Atayevich Niyazov to Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu.
Zhu asked Sarjayev to transfer regards to President Niyazov on
behalf of President Jiang and himself.  
