<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- For the first time, the Russian investigator in charge of a
corruption scandal of the Swiss construction company Mabetex,
admitted on Monday that 90 percent of the revelations on the
situation of corruption of Russian top leaders and businessmen are
true.
</P>
<P>
-- In an interview with Liberation, Commander Ahmed Shah
Massoud of Afghanistan, who has been engaged in battles with the
Taliban forces, said that he would continue the war in the eastern
provinces "up to the frontier of Pakistan" and "relaunch the
offensive in the coming days."
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The merger of the great distributors in Europe is getting to
a boiling point as the French distributors Carrefour and Promodes
announced on Monday their alliance after a rapid and smooth
discussion. Carrefour has solid positions in Asia and Latin
America, while Promodes is the largest European distributor in
France.
</P>
<P>
-- The chief of general staff of the Bosnian Serb army, General
Momir Talic, will appear on Tuesday at the Hague-based
International Court. He is the most high ranking military officer
in the conflict of former Yugoslavia ever captured by the tribunal.
</P>
