<HEADLINE> Ecuadorian President Says Visit Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Ecuadorian President
Jamil Mahuad said here today that his current state visit to China
is successful.
</P>
<P>
Mahuad said at a news conference that he discussed some
international issues with Chinese President Jiang Zemin yesterday,
and reached wide consensus.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that the Ecuadorian and Chinese governments
signed eight agreements including buyer's credit, free loans and
free assistance granted by China to Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also signed two important agreements on
cooperation in technical and agricultural areas, he noted.
</P>
<P>
"China has a huge and promising market," he added. However, he
pointed out that Ecuador has not made full use of this market
since the total trade volume between the two countries has been in
fluctuation and the mix of Ecuador's exports to China is so basic
that bananas and shrimps make up 98 percent.
</P>
<P>
"Both Ecuador and China have great interest in expanding their
two-way economic and trade cooperation," the president said,
adding that he welcomes Chinese enterprises to participate in
Ecuador's economic areas such as power, oil and telecommunications.
</P>
</TEXT>
