<HEADLINE> ICBC Launches New Consumer Credit Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) announced today that it will launch a series
of new consumer credit services in September in an effort to boost
consumption and support national economic growth.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ICBC said that they will include government
aid loans to students, comprehensive consumer loans, loans for
home remodeling, loans for tourism and holidays, small personal
loans and loans to individuals for buying houses.
</P>
<P>
The government aid loans to students, to be launched on
September 1, will be granted to college students with financial
difficulties to help pay their tuition fees and living costs.
Borrowers of the loans will enjoy discounted interest with
subsidies from educational departments.
</P>
<P>
Individual comprehensive consumer loans do not specify the use
but require some equity support or mortgage guarantee, while small
personal loans do not require guarantee but are limited to no more
than one year and no more than 20,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Loans for tourism and holidays, home remodeling and houses all
require equity support or a mortgage.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the new credit services will be
introduced on a trial basis in some of the country's major cities,
and will be gradually extended nationwide to meet consumer demand.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
