Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat Tuesday in the Egyptian port city
of Alexandria to review the results of all recent contacts between
Israel and the Palestinians on the implementation of the Wye
Accord.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said Monday that Arafat
will brief the president on all the points raised in the
Palestinian-Israeli talks.
</P>
<P>
The meeting comes two days before the trip by U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright to Egypt as part of her regional tour
with an aim of reactivating the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Egypt's mobile police patrols will begin work in
mid-September as part of efforts to restore discipline in the
streets and combat any violation of law.
</P>
<P>
Mobile patrols, each comprising an officer and four policemen,
will support security forces on the Egyptian street. They will
be under a special command at the Interior Ministry and under the
direct responsibility of security directorates.
</P>
<P>
Al-Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Leader of Sudan People's Liberation Army John Garang arrived
in Cairo Monday for talks with Egyptian officials on the latest
developments in the Sudanese peace process and the efforts exerted
to reach a comprehensive solution to the political crisis in the
African country.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old civil war between the Sudanese government
troops and the southern rebels, and famine have claimed 1.5
million lives in the poor African country.
</P>
