<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mirage Observed in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A splendid mirage stretching
several kilometers was reported in this capital city of northeast
China's Heilongjiang province at about 8:10 am on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The phenomenon lasted about half an hour and buildings, forests,
and winding mountains were observed in the mirage.
</P>
<P>
Senior engineer Lu Deshi once observed mirage in east China's
Shandong province, and he watched the splendid vision yesterday
from his apartment. "The vision is not as clear as the one I saw
in Shandong, but the scenes had to be a mirage and could not be
clouds in different shapes because they never moved for half an
hour," Lu said.
</P>
<P>
Mirage is usually seen in deserts or coastal areas and it is
very rare to be observed in cities for it requires special
conditions of sunlight and dusts and water contents in the air,
according to experts from the Heilongjiang Provincial
Meteorological Observatory.
</P>
<P>
The experts added that the recent continuous heavy rains in
Harbin could be a major reason behind the phenomenon of mirage.
</P>
</TEXT>
