<HEADLINE> New York Liberty Enter WNBA Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 29 (Xinhua) -- Crystal Robinson scored 18
points and Vickie Johnson added 13 to lead the New York Liberty to
the WNBA Finals for the second time in three years with a 69-54
victory over the Charlotte Sting in New York.
</P>
<P>
The Liberty, who had dropped the opener of the best-of-three
series at Charlotte on Friday, rallied to take the final two games
and reach the league's ultimate round after failing to qualify for
the postseason last year.
</P>
<P>
While the New York Knicks failed in five games against the San
Antonio Spurs in the NBA Finals, the Liberty are hoping to earn
their first title when they take on either Houston or Los Angeles
in the best-of-three Finals. New York lost to Houston in the
inaugural Finals.
</P>
<P>
Johnson and Sophia Witherspoon scored five points apiece during
a 14-7 run that gave New York a 54-41 cushion with 9:25 to play.
</P>
<P>
Kym Hampton, playing in what could have been her final game,
had eight points and 11 rebounds as the Liberty held a commanding
32-20 advantage on the boards after being out rebounded in each of
the first two games.
</P>
<P>
Andrea Stingson, who set a franchise record with 27 points in
Sunday's 74-70 loss, tallied 24 tonight but was Charlotte's only
player in double figures. 
</P>
