<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador Wishes to Expand Trade Ties with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadorian President Jamil
Mahuad said here on Tuesday that his government wishes to further
expand trade and economic cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Attending an economic and trade seminar organized by the China
Council for the Promotion of International Trade (CCPIT), the
president expressed the hope that his current state visit to China
will help further boost bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
"The Ecuadorian Government and people are highly interested in
strengthening economic relations with China," he said. "We also
pay close attention to the experience of China's economic growth,
which has enjoyed considerable development over the past 20 years.
"
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade between China and Ecuador has grown steadily
since the early 1990s, reaching as high as 150 million US dollars.
The trade volume was 147 million US dollars last year, down a
little from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Ecuadorian exports to China are mainly bananas and prawns,
whose export volume accounts for 98 percent of all exports to
China, according to the president.
</P>
<P>
He said Ecuador hopes to multiply its exports to China, and
export more fresh flowers and tropical fruits.
</P>
<P>
In terms of imports, Mahuad said Ecuador will purchase more
Chinese farm machines and construction machinery with credit loans
offered by China.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the president said his country welcomes Chinese
entrepreneurs to participate in Ecuador's privatization process in
the oil, electricity and telecommunications sectors, and in the
construction of airports, highways and ports.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin pledged on Monday during a talk
with Mahuad that China would vigorously support the development of
economic and trade relations in addition to pushing forward the
overall friendly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China welcomes Ecuadorian entrepreneurs to
visit and invest in China, and will encourage its own firms to
invest in the Latin American country.
</P>
<P>
China and Ecuador signed several documents on Monday, mainly on
China-Ecuador cooperation in science and technology and in the
economic field.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 Chinese entrepreneurs from across the country and
30-plus Ecuadorian businessmen and officials accompanying the
president on the visit attended the seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
