<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province, a heavy
industrial in northeast China, has named its first group of five
special inspectors to examine and supervise ten key State
enterprises in the province.
</P>
<P>
The province also named another 19 assistant inspectors for the
task, who have completed their training together with the special
inspectors at Qinghua University, and they have begun their
inspection tour around the province.
</P>
<P>
