by the Chinese government to deepen the reform of State-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The State Council dispatched such inspectors to several large
State enterprises last year and this has yielded good results.
</P>
<P>
Home to nearly 500 State enterprises, Liaoning has attracted
wide attention in reforming its debt-ridden State sector.
</P>
<P>
Lack of supervision of enterprise managers has been a
persistent problem facing the State sector, and the special
inspectors will audit the financial books of these enterprises and
evaluate the work of the managers.  
