<HEADLINE> Ecuador Begins Debt Talks With IMF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador on Monday started
renegotiating its external debt in Brady Bonuses with the
International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's external debt totals 14 billion U.S. dollars. While
suffering economic difficulties, Ecuador will propose to IMF to
restructure its Brady debt for around 5.9 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
