debts of the national bank with international private financial
institutions.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's President, Jamil Mahuad, announced last week that
from August 28 he would forestall for 30 days the payment of 90
million dollars for the interests of the Brady debt while a
restructuring is looked for.
</P>
<P>
IMF Director Michael Camdesus is scheduled to announce on
Monday the support to the Letter of Intent proposed by Mahuad.
</P>
<P>
In the near future, Ecuador will hold talks regarding a debt of
1.41 billion dollars with the Paris Club, made up of 10 creditor
countries. 
