<HEADLINE> Australian Teenagers Become Real Worriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A survey showed that the young
generation in Australia is turning into real worriers.
</P>
<P>
According to the newly published 1998 National Drug Strategy
Household Survey, among 14-to-19-year-old teenagers, there are
more than two-thirds consuming alcohol at dangerous levels.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of teenage cannabis smokers increased from 29
percent in 1995 to 35 percent last year with the proportion of
young females rising from 20 percent to 34 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, marijuana was tried by two in every five
Australians aged 14 and over, and more than half a million
14-to-19-year olds reported that they had used an illegal drug.
</P>
<P>
Among 14-to-19-year-old girls, 51 percent admitted they had
tried an illicit substance, compared with 33.5 percent three years
earlier.
</P>
</TEXT>
