<HEADLINE> ADB President Praises Sino-ADB Relationship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABIDJAN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The African Development Bank (
ADB) President Omar Kabbaj praised Sino-ADB relations in a recent
interview, and expressed his thanks for China's contribution in
the development of friendly relations and top-quality cooperation
between the sides.
</P>
<P>
Kabbaj said that China, since it joined ADB in 1985, has
continued to provide aid to African nations, which completely
fulfill the spirit of South-South cooperation. China selflessly
shares its advanced technology and experience with many African
nations, and during the cooperation with ADB, Chinese companies
have played a positive role in basic projects in poverty-
alleviation, which are considered a model of South-South
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China is one of ADB's early shareholders, which owns a one
percent share in the bank and has a 0.778 percent vote in the ADB
board. During the cooperation with the ADB, China has offered the
African Development Fund donations amounting to 185 million U.S.
dollars and contributed to helping people from 39 African nations
escape from poverty, he added.
</P>
<P>
The ADB president also recalled his visit to China in 1997,
saying that his meetings with Chinese leaders and communion with
Chinese enterprises have promoted mutual friendship between China
and the ADB. He expressed admiration for the social and economic
progress China has made in its 20 years of reforms and opening up,
saying that China has found its way to development by establishing
a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
He particularly expressed his appreciation for China's role as
a responsible country during the Asian financial crisis, which
managed to prevent the devaluation of the RMB yuan, and said this
wise and far-sighted measure has helped affected countries to
restore their confidence and end the crisis at an early date.
</P>
