<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 500 Sri Lankan migrant
workers are currently serving jail terms in foreign countries,
mostly caught for unwittingly engaging in illegal activities, said
a latest study by the Bureau of Foreign Employment.
</P>
