<HEADLINE> Brazil's GDP to Reach 4 Percent in Coming Years: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Finance
Minister Pedro Malan said Monday that Brazil is able to achieve
an annual economic growth of 4 percent in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
Malan made the remark while attending a seminar on the economic
direction, in Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
He said the country has recently suffered a major loss in its
foreign exchange as the real, Brazil's currency, lost over 40
percent of its value against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Malan stressed the three objectives of the Brazilian government,
which are to put inflation under control, to lay a solid
foundation for sustainable economic growth and to increase
investment in the social sector. 
</P>
