<HEADLINE> Greece, Ukraine to Enhance Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Greece will get two hovercraft and
even T-84 tanks and military cargo planes from Ukraine under an
accord signed here Monday on bilateral military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine promised to help Greece upgrade its military equipment
in the accord signed by Ukrainian Defense Minister Alexander
Kuzmuk and his Greek counterpart, Apostolos Tsohatzopoulos, the
Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine will sell two hovercraft to Greece in the near future
in line with the accord worth 100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the two sides are discussing the possibility of
selling Ukraine's T-84 tanks and military cargo planes to Greece.
</P>
<P>
Tsohatzopoulos, who arrived here Sunday for a three-day visit,
pledged to support Ukraine in its efforts to integrate with Europe
and develop partnership with European countries. 
