<HEADLINE> Brazil Seen to Get Good Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZILIA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's grain production will
reach 83.1 billion tons, representing a 10.5 percent surge from
the year-ago level, said a forecast of the Brazilian Institute of
Geography and Statistics (IBGE).
</P>
<P>
Brazil produced 78.2 tons of grains last year.
</P>
<P>
Due to the good harvest, Brazil's imports of agricultural
products, including rice, cotton, corn and wheat, will fall 35
percent compared with 1998.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is scheduled to buy 850 million U.S. dollars worth of
agricultural products this year, said the Brazilian National
Procurement Company. 
</P>
