<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange went down 1.27 percent to 500.85
points on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was only 12.38 million U.S. dollars against 15.548
million dollars on Friday, when the stock ended last week's
operations.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest stood at 5.65 percent in
the 24-hour term. The parity of the peso against the dollar
remained unchanged at 0.997 for purchase and 1.002 for sale.
</P>
