<HEADLINE> Four Bombs Explode in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 30 (Xinhua)-- Four devices blew up
between Sunday night and Monday dawn in Colombia, causing a lot of
property damages but no casualties, police said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Three bombs exploded minutes before midnight Sunday in front of
Barranquilla banks, in northern Atlantic province.
</P>
<P>
The fourth device was set off near Medellin subway station in
Antioquia province, where furthermore four buses were set on fire
by unidentified people in a parking lot, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
According to police reports, attackers are rebel city militias
who want to intensify tension when the workers are planning a
nationwide strike for Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The capital's authorities declared a curfew since Sunday night
until Wednesday to prevent alterations in the public order during
the protest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
