<HEADLINE> 2 Lebanese Test Positive at Arab Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Two Lebanese weightlifters
competing in the Pan Arab Games in Amman have tested positive for
drugs, Lebanon's Daily Star reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Youssef Zein and Mahmoud Shuqair were among six who were found
to have used drugs, according to officials.
</P>
<P>
They were stripped of their silver and bronze respectively in
the over -90 kilogram category.
</P>
<P>
The other weightlifters who tested positive were Assad Jaafar
of Iraq, Ahmed Abdel Salam of Egypt, Bilal Abu Raguh of Jordan and
Zahi Ammar of Algeria. They face a ban from the sport.
</P>
<P>
Drugs first made appearance in the Games two years ago in
Lebanon when five Egyptians, two Saudis, and one each from Syria,
Kuwait, Tunisia and Algeria tested positive.
</P>
<P>
This year's Pan Arab Games opened on August 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
